LOW|internal/payload/scope.go:22|ScopeFocus concatenates each scope string verbatim into the persona prompt via strings.Join with no escaping or length bound, and validation (config.go) only rejects blank/whitespace entries, not content or length. Acceptable under the trusted-operator-config threat model, but there is no length cap (a pathological multi-KB entry bloats every agent prompt) and the trust assumption is undocumented at the injection site.|Document at scope.go that scope is trusted operator input and intentionally not escaped. Optionally bound each entry's length (e.g. reject > 64 chars at config.go scope validation) so a typo cannot silently bloat prompts.|security|30|internal/payload/scope.go:12-25|claude
